<p class="opening">@PageData("description")</p>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<p>An unusual word, crewel is believed to have come from the old Welsh term 'krua' which means wool. Originally the term crewel referred to the stitching used, not the style of embroidery. Over time though, the term crewel became associated with the stunning embroidery that the heavy wool yarns created.</p>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<div class="row" align="center">
	<div class="col-md-6">
